Selectors
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>CSS Selectors Example</title>
  <style>
    /* Universal Selector */
    * {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    /* Type Selector (Element Selector) */
    p {
      font-size: 18px;
    }

    /* Class Selector */
    .highlight {
      background-color: yellow;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    /* ID Selector */
    #special {
      color: red;
      font-size: 24px;
    }

    /* Attribute Selector */
    input[type="text"] {
      border: 2px solid green;
      padding: 5px;
      margin-top: 10px;
    }

    /* Descendant Selector */
    div p {
      color: green;
    }
    

    /* Child Selector */
    div > p {
      color: purple;
    }

    /* Adjacent Sibling Selector */
    h1 + p {
      color: orange;
    }

    /* General Sibling Selector */
    h1 ~ p {
      font-style: italic;
    }

    /* Pseudo-class: :hover */
    a:hover {
      color: green;
    }

    /* Pseudo-element: ::before */
    p::before {
      content: "üëâ ";
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>This is a heading</h1>
  <p>This paragraph is not highlighted.</p>
  <p class="highlight">This paragraph is highlighted with a yellow background and bold text.</p>
  <p id="special">This paragraph has red text and larger font size.</p>

  <div>
    <p>This paragraph is inside a div and has blue text.</p>
    <p>This paragraph is a direct child of a div and has purple text.</p>
  </div>

  <h1>Another heading</h1>
  <p>This paragraph immediately follows the first heading and is orange.</p>
  <p>This paragraph is a sibling of the first one and is italicized.</p>

  <input type="text" placeholder="Enter text here">
  <input type="password" placeholder="Enter password">

  <a href="#">Hover over this link to change its color.</a>
</body>
</html>


Explanation of What Each Selector Does:
Universal Selector (*): Applies Arial font to all elements.
Type Selector (p): Sets the font size of all <p> elements to 18px.
Class Selector (.highlight): Adds a yellow background and bold text to any element with the class highlight.
ID Selector (#special): Changes the text color to red and increases the font size for the element with the id special.
Attribute Selector (input[type="text"]): Adds a green border and padding to all text input fields.
Descendant Selector (div p): Sets text color to blue for any <p> inside a <div>.
Child Selector (div > p): Sets text color to purple for direct <p> children of a <div>.
Adjacent Sibling Selector (h1 + p): Sets the color of the <p> immediately after an <h1> to orange.
General Sibling Selector (h1 ~ p): Makes all <p> siblings of an <h1> ita
licized.
Pseudo-class (:hover): Changes the link color to green when hovered over.
Pseudo-element (::before): Adds an arrow before each <p> element.
This single program demonstrates how each of these CSS selectors works in a real example.

