Media Queries

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Media Queries Example</title>
    <style>
        /* Mobile-first default styles (smaller than 600px) */
        div {
            background-color: lightblue;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 10px;
            font-size: 16px;
        }

        /* For screens 600px and wider */
        @media screen and (min-width: 600px) {
            div {
                background-color: lightgreen;
                color: black;
                font-size: 20px;
                padding: 30px;
            }
        }

        /* For screens 900px and wider */
        @media screen and (min-width: 900px) {
            div {
                background-color: lightcoral;
                font-size: 24px;
                text-align: left;
                padding: 40px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Responsive Media Query Example</h1>
    <div>
        Resize the browser window to see how this box changes styles based on screen width!
    </div>
</body>
</html>


Explanation:
Default (Mobile):

On screens smaller than 600px, the div:
Has a light blue background.
Displays text in white, centered.
Has a font size of 16px and smaller padding.
600px and Wider:

When the screen width is 600px or wider, the div:
Changes to a light green background.
Uses black text and a font size of 20px.
Padding increases for a more spacious look.
900px and Wider:

When the screen width is 900px or wider, the div:
Changes to a light coral background.
Increases its font size to 24px.
Aligns text to the left for a more desktop-style layout.
Padding increases even further for a spacious desktop experience.
How It Works:
Open the webpage and resize your browser window.
The styles will update dynamically depending on the width:
<600px: Mobile styles apply.
600px‚Äì899px: Tablet styles apply.
900px+: Desktop styles apply.
This approach ensures the design starts simple (for mobile) and progressively adds complexity for larger screens! Let me know if you need further assistance!


