<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>CSS Grid Example</title>
  <style>
    .grid-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 100px 100px 100px; /* 3 columns, each 100px wide */
  grid-template-rows: 100px 100px; /* 2 rows, each 100px tall */
  gap: 10px; /* spacing between items */
}

.item {
  background: lightblue;
  border: 1px solid darkblue;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
}
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="grid-container">
  <div class="item">1</div>
  <div class="item">2</div>
  <div class="item">3</div>
  <div class="item">4</div>
  <div class="item">5</div>
  <div class="item">6</div>
    
  
</div>
</body>
</html>

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Key CSS Grid Properties
Property	Example	Explanation
display: grid	display: grid;	Turns an element into a grid container
grid-template-columns	grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr;	Defines column sizes (fr = fraction)
grid-template-rows	grid-template-rows: 50px auto 100px;	Defines row sizes
gap	gap: 20px;	Adds spacing between grid items
grid-column	grid-column: 1 / 3;	Makes an item span multiple columns
grid-row	grid-row: 2 / 4;	Makes an item span multiple rows

